caption: Amazing place, the food and service are top notch!
Incredible food and fantastic service!

Staff are sweet and the restaurant is taking temperatures, taking down contact tracing info, and sanitizing (offering customers sanitizer packets). Socially distant and heated outdoor seats are available, as well as limited indoor seating. The pancake, chicken wings, and the banchan are tasty. Stop in for lunch or dinner!
Good pandemic bar. Outdoor space and tv that are pointed at you.

The absolute best!!! Everything from the service to the food to the drinks!! Everything is made and served with such particular attention. My server Raddy was exceptionally attentive. My party had a little bit of everything from the menu. You literally cannot go wrong here. The food was amazing! The owner of the establishment also introduced himself and served us a complimentary round of drinks and that was just more than we imagined when we made the reservation. We will be eating here again and telling our friends about it. Terrance, your passion for this business is unmatched!! See you again soon!

Best meal I’ve had in a while. The staff was wonderful and very attentive. We ordered the special lunar new year short rib, braised Spanish mackerel and vegetable pancake. They were all knockouts! Also, the house made kimchi is to die for. (We’re going to get a jar to-go the next time we’re running low.) I can’t wait to go back!  COVID precautions: They have a great outdoor setup with individual, enclosed booths with space heaters, as well as open air outdoor booths, and enclosed bubbles. The whole experience felt very safe!
Amazing food and service

Excited to order from Haenyeo. When my son placed the order, it texted him back pick up at 6:45pm. Then immediately the restaurant emailed him our order wouldn’t be ready until 7:15. An hour from when my son placed the order because they were busy. When I went to pick up the order hoping it would be ready. The hostess was rude and impatient when she couldn’t find the name of our order. She sounded exasperated with me when I asked if she had some ideas as we lived far away and had plan tonight. Saw the owner being very nice with the dining in guests. Too bad the hostess wasn’t and lost us as customers.
The sablefish was AMAZING
Delicious food. Covid safe+protected from the cold

Had an amazing dinner the food tasted great and place is very clean and classy. Every dishes great and definitely delicious than any Korean restaurant especially all seafood was assumed. Also, all of waitress and waiters were kind and good service.

Haenyeo is so good! We went in February right before the pandemic, had an excellent meal, and just went back this weekend for the first time since COVID and thrilled to the restaurant hasn't lost any of its amazing-ness! Food and cocktails are both excellent. Don't miss the japchae, chigae, and spicy pork ssam lettuce wraps. Staff is also lovely! And for the cherry on top, the Covid-friendly setup is one of the best I've seen. Warm for the winter and wall to wall separation between tables.

Great outdoor dining setup for our family of four. We loved everything we ate, especially the chicken wings, sesame noodles, bi bim bap, and kalbi. Our waiter was really nice and incredibly helpful in guiding us through the menu.

Very Very, good food.  You can tell why this has a long wait during regular times.  The food is very well flavored and balanced.  Best korean food in Brooklyn in my humble opinion.  The sundubu is very good.

I first came here a few months after it opened a few years ago and it quickly became my favorite restaurant in NYC. If you go with a group, I recommend ordering 1 small plate per person plus kimchi plus a few entrees to all share. You can't really go wrong with anything on the menu but a few personal favorites are the kimchi, wings, fried dumplings, sablefish, bulgogi, if you like spicy things, the rice cake fundido, and oh did I mention the Kimchi.  Oh and last but certainly not least, DO NOT leave until til you try the kimchi. I might have mentioned it before, not sure, but The Kimchi is literally the best kimchi IN THE WORLD. It comes as a complimentary side but make sure you ask the server for extra Kimchi.
Absolutely a spot worth stopping over, the food is good and well prepared, the rates are fair and it is regularly well organized there. Great work.
The spot is fantastic and spacious, the meals was delightful and the prices were very inexpensive. fast, effective service and very attentive staff members. I highly recommend this place.

Pretty upscale Korean place in Brooklyn with some interesting cocktails. The bulgogi especially the pork and the bibimbap are to die for. The cheesy chorizo rice cakes and classic Korean crispy wings wrap it up for a classic place to chill
The service was friendly and impeccable. The food was even better, one of the best all around meals I’ve had in quite some time. I wish I lived up the block
Innovative and delicious Korean food. Exceptional service. What a great addition to park slope.. going to visit a third time!
Amazing food and cocktails, and hidden in the back of a pub. Also, way less expensive than it would be if it were in Manhattan. How can you not love it?
Fantastic food, super nice staff members, always great character. They charge fair prices and the food quality is great. Kudos.
Second visit to Haenyeo and just as good as the first. Sat outside with socially distant seating, and incredible service. The fundido is outstanding, and the duck was RIDICULOUS.

First off, our waitress Radi was the absolute best. She is fun and sweet and we left the fate of our dinner in her hands. Haenyeo recommends one appetizer and one entree per person in terms of food quantity — we were a party of 8 and told her to surprise us, doubling items to accommodate servings for 8 if need be. She hooked it up, we feasted, we drank, AND our elaborate meal did not break the bank. With drinks included we spent $115/ea and ended up order a little more than the recommended 8 and 8 + 3 orders of the the fresh baked flourless chocolate cake. Worth every penny and every bite.  Again, everything was great, but some personal highlights included: Grilled oysters Crispy wings Rice cake fundido Seaweed stew Mackerel
Yummy!!!!!!! Get everything cause literally everything is good!
Rice cake is definitely one of the best I’ve had. Entree has big portion but overall average. Also it has a good selection of cocktails. Need to mention that I am in loooooove with their kimchi.

Haenyeo makes it difficult to support local businesses. Their wait time for food was over 45 minutes, while their regular customers received service much faster. I was surprised to find similar reviews regarding service in the past. I thought maybe this was a one-off experience but apparently it's not. The owner certainly extends their best service to the regulars, if you ever get to become one.  I'm all for local support but when multiple factors from service, time, and costs are combined, the likelihood for me to return is low. Good food especially the wings and ribs, but not special enough for me to return given the wealth of restaurants in the area.
North of good. South of great. Superb example of why a 5-star rating system stinks.
Good food and service

This place is absolutely amazing. Came here recently for a friends birthday and it did not disappoint. We ordered multiple appetizers, a couple of entrees, dessert, and everyone got a variety of drinks (I recommend Strawberry Fields) and literally every single dish was packed with flavor and deliciousness. I can't wait to come back to try the rest of the menu! Not to mention the outdoor seating is super cute with plenty of space between other parties. Our waitress was super nice (and hilarious) and even the owner came to check on us and he was just as sweet and hardworking. HIGHLY recommend stopping by here if you're in the Park Slope area.

Very well executed Korean food.  Been there about 10x since they opened - so clearly a fan.  I appreciate their focus on seafood but they have something for everyone (vegans to carnivores).  The bar is excellent as well with unique ingredient combinations and service is consistently solid.  Nice space/decor as well.
I regularly stop by purchasing some food in this place. I like the prompt customer service and well cooked dishes. Keep up the good work.
PHENOMENAL OYSTERS. GREAT FOOD GREAT SEVICE GOOD VIBEZ

This restaurant makes amazing food! The staff are super friendly and they also make delicious cocktails. I just wolfed down some take out (can't eat in yet, we are in phase 1) and can't wait to dine in! Pay them a visit and support restaurants, especially delicious ones.

I’m thinking back to my last meal in a restaurant before this pandemic. Not only was the food amazingly tasty, but the overall experience was amazing. Makes me want to go back for more! Luckily Haenyeo is still open for pick up and delivery!!!
The meals and service were beyond my expectations. We absolutely enjoyed the environment of this spot. First-rate spot to take the family out for lunch.

Thank you for reopening! Dumplings were fresh made,  Wings were great, bokumbop & fondido was delicious, and cocktails were spot on. While the pickup was a bit delayed they stepped up with a free drink. Thanks for the delicious food/drink and opening back up!
Crispiest fried wings I've ever had. Bibimbap is as good as it gets and the bouillabaisse is huge and delicious. An all-around great Korean meal

Not authentic. Too sweet. Didn’t satisfy my craving for Korean food. Pricey too. If you don’t know or care about the food tasting authentic, want a Korean restaurant that’s nicer than the typical ktown grills on the table casual fare, and live in the neighborhood, you may like it. Although there’s Insa which is better.

As a Korean-American raised in a Korean household where my mom cooked all the time and where we went to Korean restaurants for special occasions, I know good Korean food when I try it. Haenyeo has become my favorite Korean restaurant. Though they don’t have as much banchan or grilling for Korean BBQ as other restaurants, their appetizers and entrees are exceptionally tasteful and full of flavor. I rave about it to everyone!
Great Korean snacks to start, and everything I've has had been excellent
Everything was amazing. The oven baked dukboki with chorizo and oxaca queso maybe my fav

Everything I had here was amazing and I can say that without a gun to my head.  I was honestly scared to try this place at first because it seemed like an Asian fusion place but it surprised me with the quality of it's good, drinks and service again and again.  I recommend everything me and my friend got.  We got: Crispy chicken wings Kimchi pork belly soup Spicy squid bibimbap Beignets Sesame creme brulee Drinks: the schoolgirl and the seoul train  The food was amazing and the drinks tasted as good as they were strong.
Lovely place, good food, nice wine, and really great service. Good for a Friday night decompress!

First, when you walk in you notice the open layout and the warm inviting atmosphere. It is sparsely decorated, however, the decorations they do have create a cozy atmosphere great for a date or small intimate groups.  Second, service was excellent. Tommy, our waiter, made sure to attend to all our needs in an efficient manner. He successfully answered all of our questions about the menu, and he made suggestions, which enhanced our meal. He did all of the aforementioned with a genuine warmth and friendliness that made me feel at home.  Finally, the food was delicious. I had the Hanyeos Spicy Winter Bouillabaisse, with Tommy's recommendation to add the seaweed bread. The dish alone was amazing and when I dipped the seaweed bread into the Bouillabaisse it was the perfect compliment for the meal.

I had dinner last night w my best friend. EVERYONE : hostess, manager, our waiter, other waiters that came to check on us were soooo nice !! We were joking that we were going ask them what they wanted from us! Because that’s was how nice they were to us ! LOL ! The oysters were so flavorful . The perfectly crunchy triangle toasts with seaweed butter that came with t perfectly brined oysters could easily be my breakfast everyday with a cup of Irish breakfast w milk and honey 😋. We course had to try t famous queso fundido rice cake, a creation of t owner /chef. Delicious ! The bibimbap w seafood !!!!! Was AM-zing . Fresh, perfectly julienned lettuce, perilla leaves , cucumbers, carrots and topped with super fresh UNI, tuna, salmon roe and mentaiko like egg roe It was divine ! We didnt even want to mix the rice and gochuchang w t seafood cause each element was so fresh and so tasty on its own we didnt want to mix t flavors . The tofu soup had tiny little squid legs that showed t quality of material the chef sources . I am sure it was local fresh squid . It had t taste of t ocean still in those little legs . We were not drinking alcohol .( dry January hahaha ), but we drank a large bottle of water and 2 delicious herbal teas . And t bill was $75! I am not sure why some reviewers mention the food is expensive ! Of course all is relative, but if you are used to go eat at the good restaurants of NYC this bill was totally acceptable for the quality the food it was . We will be back !  It was DELICIOUS !

Ordered multiple vegetarian dishes looking for some variety. Two of the dishes were described very different but tasted like the same sauce.  Didn't get the variety of flavors I was hoping for and left some what unsatisfied for the price.

Excellent atmosphere and Delicious food. The staff could not have been better. The spicy bouillabaisse was delicious. The spicy slices of pork barbecue was wonderful and etc., Everything was terrific. Service was fine.
They serve large dishes and for fair rates. friendly employees. Will visit again.

Took us a long time to get around to come here even though we’ve had on the hit list for a while. I’d recommend you not do the same. We arrived on the later side of a Friday evening and got a table (we did call to check). It’s a lively living room like space with great “sound dampening” decorations. All the drinks are amazing and so is the food. We got the oysters and chicken, I believe the chicken was breaded with beignet - great move. Basically can’t wait to go back!

Glad to have found such an elevated Korean restaurant. They serve kimchi like the Koreans like it and they upped the oyster. The main reason I don't like this place is because of the price. It's way too expensive for what it's worth. A cute shop.
Spectacularly overpriced, mediocre Korean in /deafeningly/ loud environs.  That said, the place is pretty, and the staff are very nice.
Excellent from top to bottom! We ordered 5 small plates and 3 large ones and it was just right - not too much food. The oysters were great, as was the short rib ssam
Amazing food and service. So happy to have them in the neighborhood. Go!
Absolutely loved the food and drinks there. The waiter was also very helpful and super nice to talk to. One of my new favourite local spots!
I only have one sad blurry photo to post because the meal was so good we ate everything fast! Incredible food that’s perfect to share among a group.
Oh! Super
A little bit more expensive than other Korean place, but the food and service are great!
Amazing. Eater was right

Our experience was HELL. Waited for food for about 1 hour and manager was like food takes such long time to cook blah blah. He should've just said sorry directly and genuinely. We were not happy at all there.
Creative and original food and cocktails, with super service.

One of the best meals I’ve had in a long time. Everything delicious with some element of surprise. Great atmosphere, strong service. Touch of glamor for the Slope. A little on the expensive side, more a date place or for a special occasion.

Definitely my favorite restaurant in the Park Slope area. Haenyeo offers everything I look for in a restaurant; friendly and accommodating staff, while the atmosphere is clean, relaxing and just the right level of intimate. Most importantly the food and drinks are satisfyingly portioned, while every dish we orders was delicious. Haenyeo is great for catching up with friends, dinner date, or even a solo meal at the bar.

High expectations after the closing of beloved Do Hwa. The service was not neighborly and aloof. The errors that occurred during our dinner were sad if not comical. Curb your enthusiasm. Larry David would recommend you never order the bibimbap.
GREAT food! The saucy and spicy rice cake fundido is ridiculous.. I would eat that every day if I could. Cocktails are great. Owner is super nice and friendly, and very welcoming to guests.
Amazing place. The food is delicious, the cocktails are original and delightful and the service is impeccable. Perfect on every points. I highly recommend.
Pretty good all around, food took longer than expected (might have been a kitchen issue) but was delicious and drink were great would go back on a weekday.
LOVED all of it - spicy chicken wings,?Spicy BBQ lettuce wrap, sable fish. Non of which were spicy. Definitely coming back!
Really delicious Korean fusion! The grilled oysters are so simple but a must! The chorizo dish is also so interesting but excellent, especially when paired with the zucchini pancakes.

I'm not a big fan of Korean food personally, but oh my goodness. It's no surprise that the neighborhood is whispering about Haenyeo being on their way to being michelin star rated.  Presentation and flavor of both the food and drinks is fantastic. Definitely recommend making a reservation.
Great Korean appetizers and mains. Reasonably priced drinks. Everything we ordered was delicious. Will be back to try out the other items on the menu.
Cute Korean restaurant with some fusion flair. Very fun interior, good service and flavorful food. Particularly fun cocktail menu.
Tasty, interesting food and attentive service.  Waited much too long for dinner and dessert.
Stellar service only slightly outshines the love in the food.

I do not recommend this place for authentic korean foods or place to hang out with friends. The foods are below par. Rice on hot pot is tasteless. Pork belly stew is too salty. More importantly, the service is not impressive at all. Staffs are not friendly nor welcoming. We were served with an asian brasied hair girl, she just took the order and never came actively to check us at all. I can see her attitude on her face, if ypu dont like the job, find another one. Quality is low, price is high as compared. Do not recommend this place.

(Translated by Google) It was a different taste and feel than I thought .. The servers are kind .. The side dishes were delicious.  (Original) 생각했던거랑 다른 맛과 느낌이었고.. 서버들은 친절.. 반찬이 맛있었던걸로 봐서는 다른 메뉴들을 시도해봐야 더 정확히 알수있을거 같습니다
Excellent food and cocktails. A little uneven but ultimately very good. You will not be disappointed.
I always stop getting some food here. I enjoy the rapid customer service and well cooked dishes. Highly recommended.

I've been here twice now - once when they had just opened, and last night. After we sat down yesterday, all I could think looking at the menu was that I'd be leaving with enough tasty looking untried dishes to justify a third visit. Unfortunately I won't be making that third trip back.  The first time we went, we were sat next to a table who knew the owner and were being treated a little. Whereas our food took a while to arrive and felt a bit stilted, but the owner noticed and apologised and gave us a couple of free drinks and a dessert. We put the long waits down to opening jitters, but were impressed enough to want to return once they'd had enough time to iron out a few creases.  Fast forward a few months to last night. We sit down, order a couple of drinks and our food, and have to wait over 30 minutes for one of our small plates to arrive, suggesting the kitchen still hadn't figured things out. Although that may not be the case - yet again, we were sat next to a table who knew the owner. Despite sitting down after us, they had 5 small plates arrive practically immediately - which makes me think that maybe the kitchen is fine, our table was just bumped because the friends took priority. We ordered one of the same dishes (fundido) and despite the other table already having 4 dishes, they were given theirs while we continued to wait for any of our dishes to arrive.  Our two small plates eventually arrived (with an unimpressive gap between the two) - the pork ribs had rich and succulent meat that came right off the bone, and who can avoid the rice cake fundido? We hoped that things were getting back on track when the garnishes for the main dishes were put down shortly after we'd finished. Unfortunately it was another 20 minute wait. The jalapeno fried chicken was another solid dish - juicy, tender chicken with a nice crispy batter and a sauce with just the right amount of heat. The baby lettuce salad was a tasty and good value solution to our 'we can't just order meat dishes' conundrum.  As soon as we'd been waiting a while, our waitress routinely refused to make eye contact or ask us how things were - despite asking other tables around us that very question - and there was never an acknowledgement of the wait(s). It baffles me when service is this bad - all we needed was an apology, a free drink, or something taken off the menu and we'd probably be happy to give it another go - but I felt early on that she'd just decided to write us off for the night and pretend we weren't there. You could be forgiven for thinking we've just been unlucky, but ultimately the staff did nothing whatsoever to try and make an obviously bad situation better.  If you want delicious Korean food in Park Slope, go here - we really wanted to love this place and have it become a fixture in our local restaurants as the food more than justifies it. But every now and then you come across a restaurant that has such terrible service you leave not caring about how good the food was.
Great food, attentive service, small beer selection.

I have been to Haenyeo twice. I went back for the delicious and generous watercress salad. It is a lovely room with a kind and attentive staff. We had exceptionally good dumplings and a wonderful tofu bi bim bop (which we shared). I had a delicious cold saki recommended by our waitperson and my husband had a Korean beer. We had to move from a table in the back where the noise made it impossible for us to talk. At our table in the front, and after a particularly noisy party left, the decibel Level was much better. The meal was pricey.
We had a great dinner with friends. There is a nice mix of traditional and new dishes.
This restaurant is really, really loud.  The food is good... But conversation is impossible.
just not very good the crab was over cooked fell apart.  l don't mind paying the quality could have been better for the price
Excellent and flavorful food, I love the vibes the place has, and the staff members were very friendly. I will surely come back in the future.
Intetesting food attentive service Need to go more than once
Amazing taste not pricey at all, MUST TRY IT!!!
Tasty food, good variety and nice setting
Delicious food. Great service. Get the whole fish.
I definitely enjoyed it. Flavor-wise nothing insane or innovative, but solid classics Korean dishes with an elevated feel.

Great restaurant! I was a big fan of Dok Suni's back in the 90's and was psyched that the original owner opened a place in my neighborhood. The food is excellent and the space has a very warm welcoming vibe.
We had an amazing meal this week. The fundido was so flavorful I haven't stopped thinking about it, cocktails were delicious,- can't wait to go back and try other dishes!
Incredible variety of food, super nice staff, and spacious setting with lots of natural light. We got the beef lettuce wraps and the sashimi bibimbap (spicy in the best way) and loved it all.

Very good food. Menu slants toward seafood. But it isn't cheap ($90 for two entrees and one appetizer and one dessert, no alcohol). Like all Korean restaurants there is generous extras of vegetable small dishes that arrive between appetizer and entree, including two sorts of kimchi. Fish was wonderful, especially the mackerel but also the cod. Recommended but not a daily restaurant.

Great place that has a French influence in their decor as you enter. Staff is very friendly and willing to make suggestions on the food if you're not very familiar with Korean food. We went on a Sunday and were seated fairly quickly. It was busy, but didn't feel crowded. The service was a bit on the slow side, but well worth the wait! Cocktails are clever and delicious and the food was phenomenal.  Tip: Get the sesame seed creme brulee and the chicken wings. The chicken wings are so flavorful and crispy. I could eat a bucket full of them. We were lucky because they 86ed them right after we ordered them. The creme brulee tasted EXACTLY like the sesame candy I had growing up and sent me spiraling down a hole of nostalgia.  Edit: Been coming back for cocktails and creme brulee. One of the owners told me to try beignets and I am SO GLAD I did! Heavenly!

Food was overall very good, but uneven.  Pancake starters were nice, scallion better than mungbean.  Fried chicken main was very good.  Spicy tofu was also very good, though so spicy we couldn’t finish it - and I love spicy food.  Bartender was kind enough to bring a free rice drink that ameliorated the heat a bit, a nice gesture.  overall a very good experience but shy of excellent.
Friendly staff. Loved the cocktails we tried. Definitely get the oyster toast and chicken wings
Sooo happy this is a new local spot!
Simply fantastic Korean fusion in park slope. Very inventive good food, with some heat. Great cocktails. Friendly day service. Very busy.
Pretty legit Korean food. I had the bibimbop . My wife had the spicy pork lettuce wraps. Nice to find a place that rivals Koreatown in NYC. 👍👍
Amazing cocktails and food!  Queso fundido is a must have!
Everything I tasted was delicious, whether it was food or drink. Definitely worth a visit.

Really great food excellent service and well made cocktails. We managed to snag 2 seats at the window at 7pm Saturday night otherwise the wait for a table would've been btw 1 and 1.5 hours. Plus we made some new friends! Definitely try the grilled Oysters.
Would like to explore more of the menu
Ridiculously good. Will be back often.

Queso Fundido is worth the trip. The menu is small but something for everyone. Service was quick. Maybe too quick. Food overall was good but expectations weren't met at first taste. I like the clean white atmosphere the space was welcoming. I would go back but rating just okay for now.
Great service!
New spot in Park Slope. Food was delicious.
Nice classy atmosphere. Good quality food. Average cocktails

Great food and great service. Came here on a Tuesday evening and there were many open tables. Had the kimchi pancake and pork barbeque ssam and there are both delicious. Will definitely come back to try their cocktails and the other items on their menu.

3.9.19 - Tables fill up fast for the first seating, so make sure you get there close to open if not at the open or you can be waiting up to 45-60 minutes for the next seating. They have standing tables that can accommodate parties between 2 and 6. Tonight there was a party of 10, but I'm not sure if tables were assembled to accommodate.  We ordered the crispy spicy wings, zucchini pancake (flavorless, requires the sauce), jalapeno chicken, short rib bbq with lettuce wraps, and spicy soft tofu seafood stew. Everything was very good. The beef was very tender; both chickens were tender and juicy; and the pancake was not oily, but it needed the sauce that came with it to add savoriness.  The cocktails are okay, nothing that stands out. The staff is on point. The kitchen took a little bit of time to push out our entrees, mainly because everyone sat at the same time, and I'm assuming all the orders were put in almost at the same time, too, so there was definitely bottleneck or something else happening in the back.  I will repeat  to try the rest of the menu, but there's nothing that has the power of the Force to bring me back.
Needs a better system for waiting for tables, but good tasting food and drinks.

Beautiful place with great food! A friend and I sat at the bar one Thursday night and had some amazing apps and dessert. My only problem is neither of us liked our main courses.  Get the grilled oysters- you won’t be disappointed

Came here with my daughter who is a real trooper about trying new foods. Arrived around 7pm on a Sunday.  No wait and very attentive service.  We started with the short rib dumplings and scallion/zucchini pancakes. Both were delicious. Main course was vegetarian bimbop and sea bass.  The fish was cooked to perfection.  The bimbop so satisfying with the accompanying Kimchee, burdock root, fried squid and pickled Dachon radish.  Strongly recommend.
(Translated by Google) How good is wrong  (Original) 都几好唔错

Great food, great drinks, and great service. My friends and I walked in on a crowded Saturday night and sat at the bar. I started with a 1st and 7th cocktail and could help but order another—it was that good—and we all shared a bunch of the small plates. This is the perfect place for a date night or to catch up with friends.
Spicy new addition to the neighborhood.  Chorizo app is fiery hot and cheesy. Some fusion dishes. Excellent wine and cocktail selection, great service, and swanky decor.

Doesn’t take reservations, so be prepared for at least an hour wait if you go during peak times. Food is pretty good but a little slow to come out, and over all the place lacks the energy and fun of a Korean place in K-town or Flushing. Not a bad option if you’re in South Brooklyn and have a Korean food craving though, but I prefer Insa.

The wait was relatively short on a Friday night although the restaurant was fully seated. The staff were all friendly and engaging. The food took a little while to come but not a big deal. Quality is good, price is okay. Overall, not a bad experience.

The biggest flaw here is the wait but other than that the for was very good. The tofu soup was some of the best I've had however the wings were average in my opinion and the kimchi pancake was ok not the best I've had. The service excellent and bar was great however the hype for everything else might be a bit much. Some food is very good some stuff we had was good but not great so maybe my taste is different?

Loved it! Terrific addition to a neighborhood that needs some fresh choices. We had scallion/zucchini pancake, grilled oysters, short rib BBQ and bibimbop hot pot with spicy squid. The spicy squid was amazing! Simple but attractive setting and efficient servers.
I love this Korean restaurant that honors the old ladies who would still dive and forage for their food.
Fantastic, affordable dinner menu with delicious seafood and cocktails.

I had a fantastic Korean bouillabaisse that was yummy and spicy, with very fresh seafood. The glass noodles were delicious too and the braised oysters punchy. Despite how full the floor was, we were seated promptly and our food arrived soon. I'm definitely going back soon!
What can I say......just go! If need be sit at the bar, but GO!

Good food, and phenomenal service. Cheery, attentive wait staff really made it a great night out. Had the scallion pancake, gyoza, wings, and broiled mackerel. Flavors were more muted than what you'd get in K-Town, but everything worked together well, and textures were super on-point.  Cocktails also paired nicely, and were all fantastic (standouts around the table were the 1st and 7th, with the Squid & the Whale being, somewhat surprisingly, the favorite). That compared with a really pleasant ambiance contributed to an all-around great dinner.  On a side note, they accidentally brought over a dessert dish and billed us for it (we mistakenly thought it was on the house lol) but at that point we were totally fine absorbing the cost and the food haha
Amazing food, great service, will definitely be returning soon!!!
Delicious and the wait staff was super attentive ... A+

I would venture to say the one of the best, if not the best, Korean restaurants around Brooklyn. Flavorful colorful food, ample space to eat (compared to your typical NYC restaurant) and a good selection of drinks and cocktails.  Nailed the scallion pancake. Oyster appetizer had a unique flavor as it tasted of being in a tasty broth that you want to drink and eat completely. The boneless short rib was the best as that was cooked so tender with this semi-sweet Asian glazed sauce. For dessert you can customize the # of beignets you want. Good, but could use more sugar like in New Orleans.  Family friendly. Definitely gets crowded quickly, at least on a Saturday evening. Was surprised to see that on a holiday weekend! So expect a wait if you're not there right when it opens.  The price was what I expected when not eating in Koreatown, in Manhattan. Definitely costlier, but still good food and makes for a fun night. Glad when the owners closed up shop, in the West Village, they decided to open a new one in Park Slope. Great addition to the area!

The environment of this restaurant is extraordinary. Calm, yet energetic. The staff are very friendly and down to earth. However, the food is the best part. Once you take that first bite, it takes you back to Korea as if you were there with the haeneyo (female Korean divers). The barbecue has just the right amount of sweetness to sooth your taste buds, while maintaining a sharp flavor. This restaurant is true representation of Korea, and if you are hungry and ravenous, go to haenyeo. Even if you’re not hungry, the aromas will make you.
Lovely dinner, great atmosphere. Terrence and Jenny are excellent restauranteurs. You will not be disappointed!
Beautiful spot with sublime food that makes for a special and memorable evening. Wonderful addition to the neighborhood culinary scene!
They have fantastic food and the wait staff gave top tier service. This is definitely worth the price in quality of food and the dining experience.
Classic Korean dishes as well as savory new offerings in an airy elegant setting. Bringing some sexy to Park Slope!

I had a wonderful dining experience at Haenyeo.  The cocktail menu is original and delicious! Try the Squid And The Whale , a frothy effervescent homage to the neighborhood. The interior is airy and inviting . We all shared our appetizers; grilled oysters with seaweed butter , rice cakes in chili sauce with gooey cheese 😋 , amazingly crispy dumplings, perilla pancakes ; all fantastic!! The Entrees were a mix of traditional and inventive. The standouts were the Seafood Bouillabaisse , subtlety executed with loads of  mussels, clams,shrimp and Uni on top!! The grilled meat dishes were truly the best I have ever had. Portions were generous and prices right! Koreans are not known for the desert but their Beignets were light, airy and crisp . Will definitely be going back soon! IMG_5911.JPG
Beautiful fine dining with incredible quality from the outstanding chef's starter scallion pancake to the many other dishes. This is a level of Korean food I have never experienced before!
Gorgeous space and delish food with sexy cocktails

Haenyeo is barely a week old but experience from their West Village site has them up and running very smoothly already.  The food is flavorful and subtle and the service was superb.  It's already a busy place but we never felt neglected and we're eager to return.

Excellent Korean food in Park Slope. Good ambience, friendly staff. But the most important thing is the food and they get it right. The right balance between traditional Korean and something new. I'll be back soon!
